refentry.refsect1:
&reftitle.description;
SimpleXMLElement
SimpleXMLElementchildren stringns boolis_prefix
This method finds the children of the element of which it is a member. The result follows normal iteration rules.
&simplexml.iteration;

&reftitle.changelog;







     &Version;
     &Description;





     5.2.0

      The optional parameter is_prefix was added.

  &reftitle.examples;



    Traversing a children() pseudo-array


<?php
$xml = new SimpleXMLElement(
'<person>
 <child role="son">
  <child role="daughter"/>
 </child>
 <child role="daughter">
  <child role="son">
   <child role="son"/>
  </child>
 </child>
</person>');

foreach ($xml->children() as $second_gen) {
    echo ' The person begot a ' . $second_gen['role'];

    foreach ($second_gen->children() as $third_gen) {
        echo ' who begot a ' . $third_gen['role'] . ';';

        foreach ($third_gen->children() as $fourth_gen) {
            echo ' and that ' . $third_gen['role'] .
                ' begot a ' . $fourth_gen['role'];
        }
    }
}
?>


    &example.outputs;


The person begot a son who begot a daughter; The person
begot a daughter who begot a son; and that son begot a son
